{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDg2MDA5MzA4", "number": 9015, "title": "Provide a hook to shutdownJMRI and the OS", "bodyText": "@mstevetodd\nThis will shutdown and leave a return code of 200, which the script will see and run \"sudo shutdown -h\"\nI noticed the restart uses a return code of 100, which can be returned by the jvm as an error code!\nIts basically the same as shutdown, but with the return code.\nThis differs from ^C or kill -s HUP pid, in that if the user cancels when prompted due to unsaved changes it will honour that. ^C ignores the user response. All ways of cancelling will hang on a user respose if unsaved changes, which isnt good.", "createdAt": "2020-09-12T20:02:38Z", "url": "https://github.com/JMRI/JMRI/pull/9015", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "2b959159c18d5609c3c760cd81d9de197f227e01"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-09-15T21:33:02Z", "author": {"login": "Pugwash1"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 6, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdINjQJAH2gAyNDg2MDA5MzA4OjIzMTdkZTFkNDU2NDdlZGExNWM3NTRlOThlNGVjNjRmMDBlMDRmMTk=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdJJo2TgFqTQ4ODgxMzQ4OQ==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "2317de1d45647eda15c754e98e4ec64f00e04f19", "author": {"user": {"login": "Pugwash1", "name": "Steve G"}}, "url": "https://github.com/JMRI/JMRI/commit/2317de1d45647eda15c754e98e4ec64f00e04f19", "committedDate": "2020-09-12T17:35:54Z", "message": "provide a hook to restart"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NDg4MDIwNzg3", "url": "https://github.com/JMRI/JMRI/pull/9015#pullrequestreview-488020787", "createdAt": "2020-09-14T18:07:04Z", "commit": {"oid": "2317de1d45647eda15c754e98e4ec64f00e04f19"}, "state": "COMMENTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 1, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wOS0xNFQxODowNzowNFrOHRgy8g==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wOS0xNFQxODowNzowNFrOHRgy8g==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ4ODEyNTE3MA==", "bodyText": "Please add time of \"now\" to this, as in:\nsudo shutdown -h now\nThe time defaults to \"+1\" (1 minute) when not specified.", "url": "https://github.com/JMRI/JMRI/pull/9015#discussion_r488125170", "createdAt": "2020-09-14T18:07:04Z", "author": {"login": "mstevetodd"}, "path": "scripts/AppScriptTemplate", "diffHunk": "@@ -560,5 +560,7 @@ while [ \"${EXIT_STATUS}\" -eq \"${RESTART_CODE}\" ] ; do\n     EXIT_STATUS=$?\n     [ -n \"${DEBUG}\" ] && echo Exit Status: \"${EXIT_STATUS}\" | tee -a ${launcher_log}\n done\n-\n+if [ $EXIT_STATUS -eq 200 ] ; then\n+    sudo shutdown -h ", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "2317de1d45647eda15c754e98e4ec64f00e04f19"}, "originalPosition": 6}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "a01604e7cbc686967eaee554ad7e79fd5c4ac8af", "author": {"user": {"login": "Pugwash1", "name": "Steve G"}}, "url": "https://github.com/JMRI/JMRI/commit/a01604e7cbc686967eaee554ad7e79fd5c4ac8af", "committedDate": "2020-09-15T00:01:15Z", "message": "add now\nremove app and app base code. Its harder to remove it afterwards than add it if needed by a concrete example"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NDg4NjY1MjEx", "url": "https://github.com/JMRI/JMRI/pull/9015#pullrequestreview-488665211", "createdAt": "2020-09-15T13:11:17Z", "commit": {"oid": "a01604e7cbc686967eaee554ad7e79fd5c4ac8af"}, "state": "APPROVED", "comments": {"totalCount": 0, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": null, "endCursor": null, "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": []}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NDg4NzE5NzU2", "url": "https://github.com/JMRI/JMRI/pull/9015#pullrequestreview-488719756", "createdAt": "2020-09-15T14:04:42Z", "commit": {"oid": "a01604e7cbc686967eaee554ad7e79fd5c4a